<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-11T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-11T06:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60p2/28: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-11T13:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">January 11,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 11—9:30
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. Paragraph 3 of Department’s telegram No. 19, May 16, 3 p.m., 1927,
                            regarding proposed United States-Latvian commercial treaty. In
                            authorizing Legation to accept Latvian proposal regarding article 27 did
                            Department intend to approve omission of last paragraph of article 26 of
                            United States-Estonian treaty?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>